com.percussion.cms.objectstore
Class PSKey

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSKey
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSCmsComponent, Serializable, Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PSLocator, PSSimpleKey
public class PSKey
extends Object
implements IPSCmsComponent, Serializable

This class is used to store a multi-part identifier for a component. Each part of the key has a unique name (within an instance). In general, the key parts are the column names of the primary key for a specific component type.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Paul Howard

Constructor Detail

PSKey

public PSKey(String[] definition,
             String[] values,
             boolean persisted)
Creates an assigned key. An assigned key has values for the key parts. The constructed object will not need generate id, needGenerateId() return false.

Parameters:
definition - The names of the parts that make up this key. Each entry in the supplied array must be a non-null, non-empty string.
values - The values for each key part. The i'th value must correspond to the i'th entry in the definition. Each entry in the supplied array may be null or empty.
persisted - A flag to indicate whether this key represents a component that exists in the db. Realize that this is a snapshot, so the component represented by this key could be removed while this key is instantiated.

getPartCount

public int getPartCount()
Each key is made up of 1 or more named parts. This method returns the # of parts in this key.

Returns:
a positive integer.

isAssigned

public boolean isAssigned()
This method is used to determine if this key instance has a value or is just a definition. If the isPersisted() method returns true, this method is guaranteed to return true.

Returns:
true if this key has values assigned for its parts, otherwise false.

isPersisted

public boolean isPersisted()
A persisted key is one that references an existing db component (at the point in time that the key was created). If the state of the object is known to change, the setPersisted method can be used to resynchronize the key with the db.

Returns:
true if this key references a component that exists in the db, false otherwise.

needGenerateId

public boolean needGenerateId()
Determines whether the object need a generated id or not.

Returns:
true if it does need the id; false otherwise.

getPart

public String getPart(String name)
Gets the value for a particular part of this key. If the key is unassigned, the empty string is returned.

Parameters:
name - The name of the key part for which you want the value. Never null or empty. If the supplied name is not a part of this key, an exception is thrown. The comparison is done case- insensitive.
Returns:
The value for the named part, or "" if no value has been assigned.

getDefinition

public String[] getDefinition()
Gets the names for all the parts making up this key.

Returns:
An array whose length is equal to the value returned by getPartCount(). If the key is assigned, each entry is a name with 1 or more chars, otherwise, all entries are "".

isSameType

public boolean isSameType(PSKey key)
Compares only the definition of the supplied key with this key.

Parameters:
key - May be null.
Returns:
If all the parts of the supplied kay and this key have the same name (case insensitive compare) and are in the same order, true is returned. Otherwise, or if null, false is returned.

toXml

public Element toXml(Document doc)
Serializes this object into an xml element that can be attached to the supplied document. It will conform to the following dtd: 
 <!ELEMENT PSXKey (Property+)>
 <!ATTLIST PSXKey
    isPersisted        (yes|no) yes
    needGenerateId     (yes|no) no
    >
 <!ELEMENT Property (#PCDATA)>
Where Property is the name of various definitions. the needGenerateId attribute only needed for non-persisted key object.

Specified by:
toXml in interface IPSCmsComponent
Parameters:
doc - Used to generate the element. Never null.
Returns:
the generated element, never null.

fromXml

public void fromXml(Element src)
             throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
This method is called to recreate a previously persisted instance. The supplied xml node was typically generated by a previous call to the toXml method. Say you have 2 instances of this class, A and B. After calling B.fromXml(A.toXml), it is guaranteed that A.equals(B) will return true.

If a base class implements this method, the derived class should, but doesn't have to, call the base class to perform the de-serialization. If the base class doesn't implement this method, the derived class is responsible for restoring the base class (in this case the base class must have methods allowing the derived class to properly restore the state). Whatever technique is used, it should be symmetrical w/ the toXml method, meaning both methods must call the base class or not.

The name of the element supplied should be the same name returned by the getNodeName method.

Every class implementing this interface must also create a single arg ctor that takes an Element. The implementation of this ctor should call super(elem) followed by fromXml(elem).

Specified by:
fromXml in interface IPSCmsComponent
Parameters:
src - The node to extract the data for this instance. Never null. See toXml for the required format of the supplied element.
Throws:
com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException - If the name of the supplied element is incorrect or any of its attributes or children are required but missing or incorrect.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Since it is expected that derived classes will only add behavior (and not data) that makes this class easier to use in specific situations, this method assumes that no data outside this class needs to be compared when checking equality.

This allows instances of derived classes to be equivalent to instances of this class where a typical implementation would be asymmetrical.

If a derived class has additional data that must be considered, it should override this method and call it, then test the additional data it has.

Specified by:
equals in interface IPSCmsComponent
Overrides:
equals in class Object
Parameters:
obj - the reference object with which to compare. May be null;
Returns:
true if this object is logically equivalent to the supplied obj; false otherwise. If null or not an instance of this class, false is returned.

hashCode

public int hashCode()
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
Must be overridden to fulfill contract of this method as described in Object. The following method should be used to calculate the hash code.
  1. Get the hashcode from the base class (unless the base class is Object).
  2. Add this hash code to the sum of all hash codes obtained from all non-native types.
  3. Add to this result the hash code obtained by creating a concatenated string of all native types and taking the hash code of that.

Specified by:
hashCode in interface IPSCmsComponent
Overrides:
hashCode in class Object
Returns:
A hash code value for this object that will work correctly for maps.
